revisions.rev:
The '''Mid-American Conference football awards''' are given annually by the [[Mid-American Conference]] (MAC) at the conclusion of each [[college football]] season. The conference gives out a total of five awards, the Offensive, Defensive, and Freshman Players of the Year, the Coach of the Year, and the Vern Smith Leadership Award, which is given to the league's [[MVP]] in that season. The Vern Smith Award is selected by a vote of the coaches in the MAC while the remaining awards are selected by the MAC News Media Association.<ref name="2009 awards" group="ref"/>
== Offensive Player of the Year == [[File:Byron Leftwich.jpg|thumb|upright|Byron Leftwich is one of the few multiple Offensive POTY award winners. He earned a Super Bowl ring with the Pittsburgh Steelers in 2009.]] [[File:Nate Davis at 49ers Family Day 2009 2.JPG|thumb|upright|Nate Davis led the Ball State Cardinals to an undefeated regular season in 2008, earning him the Offensive POTY award in that year.]]
